JavaScript and the DOM

- Handy Function: console.log()
    - access JavaScript console in your browser

Basic Syntax
- semicolon is optional ; 
- tabs dont matter, important for readability
- single line comments //
- multiline comments /**/
Variables
- NEVER USE var
- let obeys scopes, improves code predicatability
- const dont change

Document Object Model - DOM
- how JavaScript interacts with HTML and CSS
- HTML elements/nodes can be obtained either through queries or tree navigation and stored
- Elements/nodes can have their attributes/CSS properties manipulated as if they were JavaScript objects
- JavaScript must be running